📌 PROJECT NAME: GreenScrapHub – Scrap Pickup & Delivery System

Built with:

Backend: Node.js (ESM) + Express + MySQL

Frontend (coming later): React Native App for Customer, Rider, Agent

Admin Panel: Will be added later

Authentication: Login via phone number

Roles:

admin

agent

rider

customer

📌 CURRENT MODULES COMPLETED
✅ 1. Auth Module

Phone + password login

auth/me endpoint

JWT token-based auth

Works for all roles

✅ 2. User Table Structure
id
full_name
phone (unique)
email (nullable)
password_hash
role (admin/agent/rider/customer)
agent_id (nullable – used only for riders)
created_at
updated_at

✅ 3. Agent Module

Agents are scrap collection business owners.

✓ Create Agent

When admin creates an agent:

A new user is created with role agent

An agent profile is created

✓ List Agents
Agent Table Structure
id
owner_user_id (FK → users.id)
name (company name)
email
phone
address_line
city
state
country
postal_code
commission_type (percentage / flat)
commission_value
is_active
created_at
updated_at

✅ 4. Rider Module

Riders are assigned under agents.

Rules:

Admin can create rider under any agent

Agent can only create riders under themselves

Riders get:

A user record

A rider profile

Rider Table Structure
id
user_id
agent_id
vehicle_type
vehicle_number
rating_avg
total_completed
is_online
created_at

📌 5. Customer Module

Customers are people who request scrap pickups.

✓ Customer registration by admin or agent

Creates a user with role customer

Customer profile is created

Customer Table Structure:
id
user_id
address_line (future)
area
created_at

📌 6. CATEGORY MODULE (future ready)

Admin creates scrap categories:

Examples:

Metals

Plastics

Electronics

Papers

Fields:

id
name
icon_path
is_active
created_at


Image upload supported via multer.

📌 7. SCRAP ITEMS MODULE (future ready)

Each category contains multiple scrap items.

Fields:

id
category_id
name
price_min
price_max
unit (kg/pc/ton/etc.)
image_path
is_active
created_at


API supports:

Create item

List items

List by category

📌 8. Upload System

Using multer with folders:

/uploads/categories
/uploads/items

📌 CURRENT API ROUTES DONE
/api/v1/auth

POST /login

GET /me

/api/v1/admin/agents

POST / → create agent

GET / → list agents

/api/v1/admin/riders

POST / → create rider

GET / → list riders
(admin sees all, agent sees their own)

/api/v1/admin/customers

POST / → create customer

/api/v1/categories

POST / → create category (with file upload)

GET / → list categories

/api/v1/items

POST / → create item (with file upload)

GET / → list all items

GET /category/:id → items by category

📌 BASE URL & POSTMAN CONFIG

Base URL:

http://localhost:4000


Token:

auth_token = ""


Postman collection is prepared (ready to import).

